-- Siemens Will Sign Contract With Carbon-Neutral Masdar, Handelsblatt Says
-- B y   H o l g e r   E l f e s
-- 2010-10-19T05:39:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/siemens-to-enter-deal-for-role-in-building-masdar-city-handelsblatt-says.html
Siemens AG  will sign a contract with
Masdar, a renewable-energy company backed by the Abu Dhabi
government, to play a key role in the construction of Masdar
City, the world’s first carbon-neutral city,  Handelsblatt 
reported today, citing unidentified people close to the matter.  Peter Loescher , the German company’s chief executive
officer, will sign the contract, which is worth a “high double-
digit million euros” amount, in London today, the newspaper
said. Siemens will supply electricity grids and building
services, according to Handelsblatt.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Holger Elfes  in Dusseldorf at 
 helfes@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
